Hughes Alonzo ROBINSON, Appellant v. Tommy C. MANN, Trustee, et al., Appellees. No. 21370. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Feb. 16, 1965. For former opinion, see 5 Cir., 339 F.2d 547. Hughes Alonzo Robinson, pro se. George E. Saliba, E. S. Sell, Jr., William Joseph Patterson, Jr., and John D. Comer, Macon, Ga., for appellees.

Before TUTTLE, Chief Judge, BELL, Circuit Judge, and WHITEHURST, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

It is ordered that the petitions for rehearing in the above entitled and numbered cause filed, respectively, by appellant, Hughes Alonzo Robinson, and by ap-pellee, Citizens and Southern National Bank, be, and the same are, hereby denied.
